message.body: "In BF we can read something very close to the source code no problem thanks to DNSpy. In WotW we just straight up can't. We have maps of the original C# code's functions to the addresses of the translated C++ functions. We also know in a general sense how il2cpp works so we know how the signatures get translated and how the data is structured. But the actual work was just straight up disassembling, decompiling (into C with e.g. ghidra) and reverse engineering.
